questions.question_data:
URL : https://theloom.in/


1. Build a Hybrid Automation framework using the above URL.

2. Utilize the utilities available in the framework to:

  • Read data from the Excel file,
  • Read configuration data from a property file.
  • Implement logging using different levels of log.
  • Create an extent report.
  • Create a screenshot to be used in the extent report.

3. Design at least 3 independent test cases in the framework.

4. Each test case must have a navigation of at least 2 pages.

5. Need to capture screenshots for the failed test cases.

6. Use all best practices for Log, report, properties file, excel reading and screenshot capturing.

7. Attach the screenshot to the test report file using the attachScreenshotToReport () function in the Reporter.java file from the utils folder


structured format that contains the following components in log and reports:

  • [INFO]: Log level indicating general information about the execution process.
  • Timestamp: Indicates when each action occurred, in the format yyyy.MM.dd.HH.mm.ss.
  • Class and Method: The section where the log originates, e.g., pages.Cart cart_verify or runner.
  • Action Message: Describes the specific operation performed.

        reportName = "LOOM_Application_Report"


Instructions:

1. When you open the workspace, click "ACCEPT" in the lower-right corner of the REDHAT notification to enable import package suggestions while working on Selenium scripts.

2. Ensure that you do not change the existing main class file.

3. Common Maven Commands for Selenium:

  • To change to a specific directory: cd /path of your maven project
  • To run all test cases: mvn clean test
  • To change to a parent directory: cd ..

4. To view the running scripts,

  • Click on port "8081", and you'll be directed to a new window. In the URL bar of this new window, replace "8081" with "4444" to access the Selenium Grid.
  • Perform the same procedure again, but replace "8081" with "7900" for the VNC server page
  • To view the execution, click on the "connect" button on the VNC server page.

5. If you need to terminate an active session in the Selenium Grid, you can click on the "reset grid" button located next to the "reload ide" button.

6. To execute your test scripts, click "Run Test Case".

7. To submit your code, click "Submit Project" and to end the Test by clicking "Submit Test", where you find a dialog box enter the text "END".


note :

  • Handle the pop-up by clicking the close icon.

Testcase 1:

  • Create a method named "getElementsByXPath" in utils/WebDriverHelper class,
  •  Method takes an XPath expression as a String parameter .
  • returns a List <WebElement>.


1. Launch the browser and open the url :https://theloom.in/

2.Navigate to url "https://theloom.in/buy/wedding-collection"


Product labels :


3.Get the List of All Product Label available in the page-1  using getElementsByXPath().

(also log in the report file with text :"found the list of product label" and set the STATUS : Pass)


4.Iterate through each web Element one by one from the list of product label, using Dynamic xpath.

5.Click on the First Label of product which Contains the text "Organza".


Testcase 2:

1. Launch the browser and open the url :https://theloom.in/

2. Hover on "CLOTHING" available on the top navigation bar.

3. Click on "Kaftans" under "WESTERN WEAR" section


4. In the result page, click on "Sort by" in the right side.

5. Click on the "New Arrival"


Testcase 3:

1. Launch the browser and open the url :https://theloom.in/

2. Scroll to the footer.

3.Click on "Terms & Conditions".

4. Switch to the new tab. (also log the log file with the value "switch to new tab" and set the log level as INFO). [case sensitive]

5.Wait for the page to load and Verify the Website TITLE contains the text "Terms & Condition".

6. Click "ABOUT US"

7.capture the screenshot in file name "LOOM" and attch to report in PNG format.
